              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1405910-april?shelf=for-review">for-review</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1405910-april?shelf=non-fiction">non-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1405910-april?shelf=books-about-books">books-about-books</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer70003353" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9241254059267028227">The Man who Loved Books Too Much by Allison Hoover Bartlett is a work of narrative non-fiction. This means it&apos;s most likely not going to be a snooze like your earth science textbook! I think that anybody reading this review most likely loves books. If you don&apos;t love books, why oh why are you here?<br/><a href='http://www.goodbooksandgoodwine.com/2009/09/review-of-the-man-who-loved-books-too-much-by-allison-hoover-bartlett.html' rel='nofollow noopener'>Read the rest of my review here</a></span>
  <span id="freeText9241254059267028227" style="display:none">The Man who Loved Books Too Much by Allison Hoover Bartlett is a work of narrative non-fiction. This means it's most likely not going to be a snooze like your earth science textbook! I think that anybody reading this review most likely loves books. If you don't love books, why oh why are you here?<br /><a href="http://www.goodbooksandgoodwine.com/2009/09/review-of-the-man-who-loved-books-too-much-by-allison-hoover-bartlett.html" rel="nofollow noopener">Read the rest of my review here</a></span>
