              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6080996270848260050">3 stars<br/><br/>A book that gives great information about rare books and rare book collectors, but is top heavy with incidental information. The life of Charles Gilkey - the book thief - was interesting and worth the read. This book could have easily been cut down to about 180 pages and still relayed the meat of the thief and the detective. <br/><br/>Unless you are a rare book collector I would not recommend this book. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


